# Portfolio UI/UX (CARLXAERON / CMSDS)

## Content source of truth

- Prefer **structured data** in [`src/external-config.js`](src/external-config.js) and re-exported values in [`src/config.js`](src/config.js) where applicable (`COMPANIES`, `EXPERIENCES`, `SKILLS`, etc.).
- New sections should read from config objects; avoid hard-coding long copy in JSX when it belongs in config.

## Layout and sections

- Full-page sections live in [`src/containers/Portfolio/Portfolio.js`](src/containers/Portfolio/Portfolio.js): each slide is `100vh` with `translateY` on the container.
- Section bodies typically use: `clm-fixed-hc`, `clm-inner-container`, `clm-container`, and headings inside `clm-title`.
- **Do not rely on `IntersectionObserver`** (e.g. via [`src/components/Tracker.js`](src/components/Tracker.js)) for visibility inside slides: transformed ancestors break intersection. Use `useEffect` + `setTimeout` (stagger) with `@react-spring/web` for enter animations instead.

## Styling

- **Bootstrap** grid: `row`, `col-md-*`, etc.
- **Tailwind** utilities for spacing, typography, and small layout tweaks where already used in the file.
- **SASS**: global tokens and overrides under [`src/styles/sass/`](src/styles/sass/); palette variables in [`src/styles/sass/_variables.scss`](src/styles/sass/_variables.scss) (primary / corporate blue `#1e40af` when aligned with the design).

## Motion

- Use `useSpring` / `animated.*` from `@react-spring/web` for transitions.
- Stagger list items with indexed delays (`k * 70` ms style) rather than many independent observers.

## Accessibility

- Meaningful `alt` on images; `aria-label` on icon-only controls (e.g. section nav).
- Prefer real `<button type="button">` for custom controls.

## Responsiveness

- Treat **768px** as the mobile breakpoint; `isMobile` from the zustand store in [`src/containers/Portfolio/theme-provider.js`](src/containers/Portfolio/theme-provider.js) should stay consistent with layout decisions.

## App shell

- [`src/pages/Index.js`](src/pages/Index.js) mounts the scroll portfolio at [`src/containers/Portfolio/Portfolio.js`](src/containers/Portfolio/Portfolio.js), which wraps **ThemeProvider**, modal, and **ChatAgent**. Legacy [`src/containers/Portfolio.js`](src/containers/Portfolio.js) is not the active entry.

## Theme / environment

- [`ThemeContext`](src/containers/Portfolio/theme-context.js) from [`theme-provider.js`](src/containers/Portfolio/theme-provider.js) defaults to **`env: 'prod'`** so local `npm start` matches production hero, header, and about copy. Do not reintroduce `NODE_ENV === 'development'` branching for placeholder (Lorem) content in portfolio sections.
